                    <li>Comes with ABS, EBD, dual front airbags, ISOFIX mounting</li>
                    <li>Fourth-gen variant in Europe has various passive and ADAS tech, though ANCAP/AEB ratings vary across markets</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Tata Punch</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Offers 2 front airbags, ABS with EBD, rear camera, TPMS, rear parking sensors, ISOFIX anchors</li>
                    <li>Achieved <span class="font-weight-700">5-star Global NCAP rating</span> for adult occupant protection in 2021</li>
                    <li>Also received 5-star Bharat NCAP in 2024</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Punch holds a stronger safety reputation with top crash-test scores. Swift provides standard safety features but may lag in ratings unless it's internationally tested.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Interior & Features</h2>

                <h3 class="subheading">Swift Highlights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>SHVS mild-hybrid, cup-holders, storage spaces, comfortable seats</li>
                    <li>Likely includes touchscreen infotainment, reverse camera, steering-mounted controls</li>
                </ul>

                <h3 class="subheading">Punch Highlights</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Upscale touchpoints: 10.25-inch touchscreen, Harman 6-speaker audio</li>
                    <li>Automatic climate control, sunroof (on higher trims)</li>
                    <li>Remote folding mirrors, alloy wheels</li>
                </ul>

                <p><span class="font-weight-700">Takeaway:</span> Both models offer modern interiors. Punch leans more premium with more features at higher trims.</p>

                <div class="div-line"></div>
                <h2 class="subheading">Ride & Practicality</h2>

                <ul>
                    <li><span class="font-weight-700">Swift</span> — Lower ride height is suitable for urban users. Around 163 mm ground clearance may wash over mild speed bumps but flare on potholes.</li>
